findings.recommendation:
Attach a top-level `.catch` handler to every `start()` invocation so startup failures are visible and logged:
```js
start().catch((error) => {
  console.error('[app] Fatal startup error:', error);
  // Optionally render a visible error state in the DOM
});
```
Both the `DOMContentLoaded` callback path and the synchronous else-branch need this treatment.

Introduce a one-shot guard so `disconnect()` is called at most once per provider instance:
```js
let handled = false;
provider.on('connection-close', (event) => {
  const reason = String(event?.reason || '');
  if (handled || !NON_RECONNECT_CLOSE_REASONS.has(reason)) return;
  handled = true;
  provider.disconnect();
});
```

Post a richer error payload that captures all available diagnostic context:
```js
self.postMessage({
  error: {
    message: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),
    stack: error instanceof Error ? error.stack : undefined,
    name: error instanceof Error ? error.name : 'Error',
  },
  renderVersion,
});
```
The main thread should log all fields, not just `message`.
